            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I am sadden to say this but the school is not what it says. I wanted to admit my child in Prakriya. After the written and oral exam, without proper assessment the school as branded my child has \"Autism\" during the admission process. And was told to admit him in a special school who is already going to a normal school. A child specialist has already assessed and evaluated my child saying he does not have autism. I am happy that my child is not admitted in such a school where the people are narrow minded and label children without proper assessment. It is great loss for the school not for my child.",
